This Node.js application provides APIs for user sign-up and sign-in functionalities. It allows users to register with their first name, last name, email, and password, and then authenticate themselves using their email and password.

Setup Instructions:
1. Clone Repository: git clone https://github.com/ShwetaPokale/myapp.git

2. Install Dependencies: Navigate to the project directory (cd /myapp) nd install the required dependencies using npm
npm install

3. Run the Application: Start the server by running the following command:
npm start or node server.js

APIs
1. Sign-Up
Endpoint: POST /api/signup
Request Body:
{
  "first_name": "ABC",
  "last_name": "XYZ",
  "email": "abcxyz@gmail.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

Description: Register a new user with the provided details.

2. Sign-In
Endpoint: POST /api/signin
Request Body:
{
  "email": "abcxyz@gmail.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
Description: Authenticate a user with the provided email and password.

Deployment
This application is deployed using Render. 
https://myapp-abh7.onrender.com

Testing
Postman Collection: A Postman collection is provided in the repository for testing the APIs. Import the collection into Postman to run the requests.

https://myapp-abh7.onrender.com/api/signin
https://myapp-abh7.onrender.com/api/signup


